Void.fill(Object[] array, Object val): assigns the specified Object reference to each element of the specified array of Objects.
Void.sort(Object[] array): sorts the specified array of objects into ascending order, according to the natural ordering of its elements.

boolean.equals(Object[] array1, Object[] array2): returns true if the two specified arrays of Objects are equal to one another.

String.toString(Object[] array): returns a string representation of the contents of the specified array.
